<h2>RSVP</h2>
<p>Use our <a href="{$root}/site/wineconf/rsvp">RSVP Form</a> to let us know you plan on attending this year.  Limited funds are available for those needing
 travel assistance.  Please make a note in the comment field of the form if
 you're interested.   </p>

<hr />
<h2>Agenda</h2>
<p>At this point the plan is to have a somewhat open schedule with time for informal
discussion.  We'll likely structure the conference similar to last year's with a set of
formal presentations with plenty of time at the end of each for questions.  Last year
we had about a 10 presentations and that number will likely remain about the same.  As
we get closer to the conference we'll announce a formal agenda.</p>



<hr>
<h2>Remote Participation</h2>
<p>After last year's failure to provide real time audio and video streaming, we will
not be making that a priority this year.  We will have networking available within
the conference room and many people will be on IRC.  </p>



<hr>
<h2>Discussion</h2>
<p>We have established a 
<a href=http://www.winehq.org/mailman/listinfo/wineconf>mailing list 
specific to Wineconf</a>.  We recommend that anyone planning on attending
subscribe, as this will be where we discuss and develop details on the program.
This will also be a great place for people to connect to share rides and or
coordinate travel schedules.</p>




